DNS.display: An Internet host name, in accordance with RFC 1035; or an IP address. Either in ASCII or as integers, with periods between components (“dotted” notation).

CLIP.display: Clinical laboratory Improvement Program. Allows for the ability to designate organization identifier as a “CLIP” assigned number (for labs). Used by US Department of Defense.

Random.display: Usually a base64 encoded string of random bits. Note: Random IDs are typically used for instance identifiers, rather than an identifier of an Assigning Authority that issues instance identifiers

x400.display: An X.400 MHS identifier. Recommended format is in accordance with RFC 1649

ISO.display: An International Standards Organization Object Identifier (OID), in accordance with ISO/IEC 8824. Formatted as decimal digits separated by periods; recommended limit of 64 characters

HCD.display: The CEN Healthcare Coding Scheme Designator

CLIA.display: Clinical Laboratory Improvement Amendments. Allows for the ability to designate organization identifier as a “CLIA” assigned number (for labs)

EUI64.display: IEEE 64-bit Extended Unique Identifier is comprised of a 24-bit company identifier and a 40-bit instance identifier. The value shall be formatted as 16 ASCII HEX digits, for example, “AABBCC1122334455”. The 24-bit company identifier, formally known as Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI-24), is guaranteed to be globally unique. The 40-bit extensions are assigned by manufacturers. This identifier is often used in equipment interfaces (e.g., “MAC” address format for IPv4 & IPv6). [See http://standards.ieee.org/regauth/oui/tutorials/EUI64.html for a detailed explanation of the format.]

UUID.display: The DCE Universal Unique Identifier, in accordance with RFC 4122. Recommended format is 32 hexadecimal digits separated by hyphens, in the digit grouping 8-4-4-4-12

U.display: Status Change to Final Without Retransmission

Y.display: Yes, patient has a living will

I.display: No, patient does not have a living will but information was provided

N.display: No, patient does not have a living will and no information was provided

F.display: Yes, patient has a living will but it is not on file

NNxxx.display: National Person Identifier where the xxx is the ISO table 3166 3-character (alphabetic) country code

UPIN.display: Medicare/CMS (formerly HCFA)’s Universal Physician Identification numbers

DFN.display: Drug Furnishing or prescriptive authority Number

2076-8.display: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander

TF.display: technology fee for use of equipment

UP.display: unit price, may be based on length of procedure or service

17.display: Minor dependent of a minor dependent
